British Petroleum Co Plc &lt;BP.L> sharesfell sharply in early trading, in response to last night's newsthat the U.K. Government will sell its remaining 31.7 pct BPholding during the financial year starting next month, dealerssaid.    By about 0840 GMT, BP shares were down to 802p, 26p belowlast night's close of 828p and 14p lower than the openingquote. The long-rumoured sale was announced by the governmentat the end of the second day of the budget debate inParliament.    At last night's closing price, unofficial estimates put thevalue of the government shares in BP at around 4.8 billion stg. REUTER&#3;